.TH BANNERHUNTER 1 "March 2026" "BannerHunter" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
bannerhunter \- safety-first single-target banner & service probe
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bannerhunter
.B --i-have-permission
.B -h
.I host
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
BannerHunter connects to a single authorized target host and attempts to read service banners on specified ports.
It can optionally negotiate TLS, send a CRLF to trigger banners, and probe HTTP via a HEAD request.
.SH REQUIRED
.TP
.B --i-have-permission
Acknowledge explicit authorization to test the target.
.TP
.BR -h ", " --host " " host
Target hostname or IP.
.SH PORTS
.TP
.BR -p ", " --port " " n
Scan a port (repeatable).
.TP
.BR -P ", " --ports " " spec
Comma list and ranges (e.g. 80,443,8000-8100).
.TP
.B --default-ports
Scan a curated default set of ports.
.SH TLS
.TP
.B --tls
TLS only.
.TP
.B --no-tls
Plain TCP only.
.TP
.B --sni
Override TLS SNI.
.TP
.B --show-cert
Print TLS cert subject and issuer.
.SH PROBING
.TP
.B --probe-http
Send HTTP HEAD request after connect.
.TP
.B --send-newline
Send CRLF after connect.
.SH OUTPUT
.TP
.BR -o ", " --output " " file
Append output to file.
.TP
.B --jsonl
Emit JSON Lines.
.TP
.BR -q ", " --quiet
Reduce non-result output.
.SH SEE ALSO
README.md, docs/USAGE.md
